description: there's Lee's second wicket, and Woakes again was trying to steer it to third man but this ball bounce more than he expected and nipped away a touch, he's got an edge through to Haddin
bouncer and it's caught behind! Watson has two in his first over! Woakes has tried to hook this one and got a tickle through to Haddin
the arm ball working for Jadeja again, tossed up, Woakes forward to defend, hit in front of middle, and gone

astounding catch from the New Zealand skipper, short ball coming into the batsman, Woakes edges and McCullum initally appears wrong-footed but recovers remarkably to snaffle a one-handed take as the ball settles in his right palm

oh, Kelly, what have you done! Woakes attempts to hit Mills into the Abbey Road, he's nowhere near the pitch and it comes off somewhere near the bottom of the bat, sails high into the off side and is safely pouched by the cover sweeper coming in. England lose a fourth batsman in the 30s

comes down the track, drifts past the bat and he's well out of his ground as Ronchi completes the stumping - that's all, Woakes! Think the bowler saw him coming, dragged it wide and there was no turn, skidded through to the keeper and this time he finishes the job without any alarums

big spin! That's a lovely delivery. Another England batsman left groping at spin. This one really gripped around off stump, spun sharply away, Woakes had dragged out of his crease and it was a simple stumping for Dhoni

picks out the fielder! Mohit having a good day in the field. A short ball from Shami, Woakes pulled it out of the middle of the bat but didn't picked the gap and couldn't keep it down so found Mohit just in front of deep square
bulls eye! Another yorker and this time bang on middle stump, Woakes wasn't worried about his toes, having stepped away, but was summarily cleaned up

tossed up, lures Woakes down the wicket, he's beaten and what a stumping! Herath deceived both batsman and keeper with a lovely flighted ball that pitched on middle and leg and turned across the off stump, Woakes played to leg, missed and fell out of his ground but then Sangakkara - who was headed down the leg side - darted his hands to his right to take the ball and whip off the bails, superb work behind the stumps, and a beauty of a delivery

just as the stand was building, and Bopara needed support, Woakes charges down the pitch and is beaten leaving Sangakkara which a simple stumping. Hang on, the umpire wants to check the no-ball. It's very tight, is anything grounded behind the line? This would be very careless from Mendis. The foot drags forward a touch, and it's ruled to legal. Just.

a very slow loopy delivery that Woakes tries to slap into the leg side and he's bowled, missing it by a mile really. Couldn't pick up the pace of the delivery, swung right across it and got cleaned up, Woakes has really struggled with spin this tour

forward press, pushed back in the air to the bowler and taken low down! A smart return catch, indecision from the batsman, neither tried to belt it nor carefully steer it and pays the penalty. Innocuous off stump delivery, Woakes just misjudged the stroke and tapped it back a foot from the floor, Dilshan down well for the save

dance down the pitch, the bowler saw him, fired it right in the blockhole and clean him up! Woakes has played pretty well but now forced to try and raise the tempo, comes down and aims a drive into the off side, the quicker ball beat him and knocked out leg stump
Woakes has given it away! Pretty innocuous delivery on middle and leg, Woakes went back and worked it to leg but in the air and straight to midwicket for an easy-peasy catch

and now he is on a hat-trick too, Glenn Maxwell, how soft is this, Woakes has leaned forward and just popped back this offbreak straight to the bowler, horror game for Woakes this, 0 for 89, and now this

slower ball outside off, lifted a bit too high into the air and well, don't bother it's Smith under it having back-pedalled from mid-off. So it's bound to be taken. Beaten for the lack of pace and England's fiesty resistance seems to be at an end

Southee. Unplayable Southee. Has a Michelle now. Four of them have been bowled to outswingers that have hit the off stump. That's beautiful. Outswingers hitting the top of off. Too good for a No. 8. Woakes' only mistake here is, he is not forward. Southee loves it. Gives him the space to let this outswinger drop and then move past the outside edge to hit the top of off. Nothing wrong in the pitch here. Just high-quality swing bowling and aggressive captaincy
another ball, another top edge, another catch by Mommsen! He runs to his right from extra cover towards mid-off and takes another steepler. Same finish too. Falling backwards as he completed that

he's on a hat-trick! Short, angled down the leg side, Woakes goes for a paddle-turned-pull and gets a very thin glove through to Wade. One glove down the leg side can be unlucky, but two in four balls?

is that out? Given. Woakes goes now. England falling apart. Woakes looks to swivel-pull the ball into the leg side but gets a thick inside edge which carries low to Wade. Lord's is quiet. The Stokes dismissal has had a bearing impact on the game.

banged in short, Woakes sticks up his bat like a periscope - and tickles it to the keeper! Rabada breaks the stand at 95, a bit too quick for Woakes, I think, and his lollipop across the line comes to grief. He's done a fine job of staving off a complete collapse, though

would you believe it! It's a poor ball, full on leg stump, and Woakes just clips it straight to the man at long leg. He didn't have to move. Wiese is almost embarrassed that the ball took a wicket, but he won't mind in the slightest
dragged on! Pakistan keep chipping away. A slower ball outside off, Woakes early on his drive and gets an inside edge into the timber
what a spell this is! On a good length at off stump, Woakes trying to run it down to third man and gets a healthy nick through to the keeper
off stump goes back! Another subtle change of pace. It's a length ball at off stump, Woakes tries to heave to the leg side and is far too early on the stroke. Excellent delivery

short ball, Woakes pulls from wide of off stump, loops h-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-g-h out towards deep midwicket - where it is superbly taken diving forwards! Not in control of that, Bishoo doing very well to hold on
picks out deep cover! Woakes hit that pretty well, but straight to the fielder this time

slower ball, slugged down the ground... and well taken by the fielder running in from long-on! Glenn Maxwell it is, on as a sub, and he's the sort of catcher you want under those. Woakes' impressive counterattack is ended, a wide legcutter from Tye does it and he picks up his second wicket

does him with the slowy! Woakes is looking for the drive over extra cover, because there is width on the ball. Problem is there is no pace, and those shots need pace to time properly. Boult secures the inside edge, and then the catch reaching to his right
low full toss does the trick! Williamson kept his close catchers in position, and he himself intercepts an urgent slap at short cover. Another timely breakthrough to put a dent in England's progress

chips to long-on! Someone in commentary screeches "Crazy! Bizzare!" and he isn't wrong. A half-hearted lift on the up from Woakes, to long-on's left. A regulation length ball, hit with no real purpose. Unless the purpose was to get it further than 30 yards, in which case he's succeeded by quite a way. Boult sprints in and to his left to hold on. And then he brings out the smile
